      "articles": [
        "Article I — Scope of Enterprise",
        "Article II — Prohibited Activities",
        "Article III — Core Identity",
        "Article IV — Human Authority Reservation"
      ]
    },
    "priority": {
      "criticality": "CRITICAL",
      "urgency": "IMMEDIATE",
      "impact": "ORGANISM_IDENTITY_ABSENT"
    },
    "reasoning": "Without defined scope and prohibited activities, the organism has no constitutional limits, posing unbounded risk. The missing core identity prevents any self-constraint; the missing human authority reservation removes the formal mechanism for human override. In the current scaffold state, the DIO could theoretically interpret any action as permissible, which violates the foundational safety architecture that requires a human-authored BoR before any operational governance can function. The empty goal-stream does not mitigate this gap—it merely delays exposure. Constitutional identity must be established before any operational goals are introduced."
  }
